## Timeline

Just container.

```
Timeline
- id
- storyId
- name
- title
- index (int)
```

---

## Branch (Semantic Only)

```
Branch
- id
- timelineId
- name
- title
- parentBranchId
- level (1-3)
- orderKey
```

No flow logic here.
Just grouping.

---

## Leaf

```
Leaf
- id
- branchId
- name
- title
- orderKey
- node (Nodes[])
```

Leaf is your graph canvas.

---

## Node

```
Node
- id
- leafId
- eventId? (nullable if connector)
- type: START | END | EVENT | CONNECTOR
```

---

## Edge

```
Edge
- id
- fromNodeId
- toNodeId
- type: CHRONOLOGICAL | RELATIONSHIP
```

That’s it.


Edges define movement.

This model supports:

* Single
* Multi
* Branch
* Split
* Merge
* Cross-leaf connectors
* Parallel duplicates

Without hacks.

